  "text": "LLVM Pass Manager Registration and Execution Chain\n\n## PassManager Template Architecture\n\nThe core pass management system is built on a template-based architecture defined in llvm/include/llvm/IR/PassManager.h. The PassManager<IRUnitT, AnalysisManagerT, ExtraArgTs...> template (lines 159-226) implements a generic pass manager that can manage passes over any IR unit (Module, Function, Loop, etc.). This template provides:\n\n1. **addPass() method** (lines 193-214): Accepts a pass instance and wraps it in a PassModel concept wrapper, storing it in a std::vector for sequential execution\n2. **run() method** (lines 190-191): Executes all contained passes sequentially over the IR unit, propagating the AnalysisManager to each pass for dependency resolution\n3. **PreservedAnalyses tracking**: Each pass reports which analyses it preserves, enabling the AnalysisManager to invalidate stale results\n\nThe ModulePassManager typedef (line 238) is a convenience specialization for Module-level passes: `using ModulePassManager = PassManager<Module>;`\n\n## PassRegistry Registration System\n\nPass registration follows a two-tier system defined in llvm/include/llvm/PassRegistry.h and implemented in llvm/lib/IR/PassRegistry.cpp:\n\n1. **PassInfo metadata** (llvm/include/llvm/PassInfo.h, lines 29-89): Each pass has a PassInfo instance containing:\n   - PassName: Display name of the pass\n   - PassArgument: Command-line argument to invoke the pass\n   - PassID: Type-erased identifier (&MyPass::ID)\n   - NormalCtor: Default constructor function pointer\n\n2. **PassRegistry::registerPass()** (llvm/lib/IR/PassRegistry.cpp, lines 48-62): Global singleton registry that maintains two maps:\n   - PassInfoMap: Maps PassID (void*) to PassInfo pointer\n   - PassInfoStringMap: Maps PassArgument (StringRef) to PassInfo pointer\n   - Listeners: PassRegistrationListener callbacks for observers\n\n3. **Registration macros** (llvm/include/llvm/PassSupport.h, lines 39-58):\n   - INITIALIZE_PASS_BEGIN/END: Defines a pass initialization function that creates PassInfo and registers it\n   - RegisterPass<T> template (lines 89-98): Simple registration helper that calls PassRegistry::registerPass()\n\n## Pass Concept and Polymorphism\n\nThe pass system uses concept-based polymorphism (not inheritance) defined in llvm/include/llvm/IR/PassManagerInternal.h:\n\n1. **PassConcept** (lines 40-63): Abstract interface for pass objects with virtual methods:\n   - run(IRUnitT&, AnalysisManagerT&, ExtraArgTs...): Executes the pass\n   - printPipeline(): Prints pass name for debugging\n   - isRequired(): Indicates if pass should skip instrumentation\n\n2. **PassModel<IRUnitT, PassT, AnalysisManagerT, ExtraArgTs...>** (lines 72-114): Type-erased wrapper that adapts any pass object conforming to the run() protocol into the PassConcept interface. This enables storing heterogeneous pass types in a single vector.\n\n## Pipeline Construction: PassBuilder\n\nThe PassBuilder class (llvm/include/llvm/Passes/PassBuilder.h) orchestrates standard optimization pipelines:\n\n1. **buildPerModuleDefaultPipeline()** (llvm/lib/Passes/PassBuilderPipelines.cpp, lines 1715-1761):\n   - Entry point for O0-O3 pipeline construction\n   - Calls buildModuleSimplificationPipeline(Level, Phase) at line 1746\n   - Calls buildModuleOptimizationPipeline(Level, Phase) at line 1749\n   - Returns a ModulePassManager containing the complete pipeline\n\n2. **buildModuleSimplificationPipeline()** (lines 1091-1474):\n   - Adds early canonicalization and cleanup passes\n   - O3-specific: CallSiteSplittingPass at line 1152 (only for O3)\n   - Includes: ForceFunctionAttrsPass, InferFunctionAttrsPass, IPSCCPPass, GlobalOptPass, etc.\n\n3. **buildModuleOptimizationPipeline()** (lines 1478-1700):\n   - Adds late-stage optimization passes after inlining\n   - O3-specific: ControlHeightReductionPass at line 1566 (EnableCHR && Level == OptimizationLevel::O3)\n   - Includes: PartialInlinerPass, loop optimizations, vectorization (addVectorPasses), LoopSinkPass\n\n## Execution Order in O2/O3 Pipeline\n\nThe standard optimization pipeline for O2 and O3 follows this order:\n\n1. **Module Simplification Phase**:\n   - Annotation2MetadataPass\n   - ForceFunctionAttrsPass\n   - InferFunctionAttrsPass, CoroEarlyPass\n   - Function-level simplification (EarlyCSE, SROA, SimplifyCFG)\n   - CallSiteSplittingPass (O3 only)\n   - IPSCCPPass, GlobalOptPass, DeadArgumentEliminationPass\n   - Function attribute inference (FunctionAttrsPass)\n   - Jump threading, GVN, DSE\n\n2. **Module Inlining Phase**:\n   - ModuleInlinerWrapperPass with CGSCC passes\n   - Post-inlining simplification\n\n3. **Module Optimization Phase**:\n   - PartialInlinerPass\n   - ReversePostOrderFunctionAttrsPass\n   - Function optimization pipeline:\n     - Loop optimizations (LoopRotate, LoopDeletion, LoopInterchange)\n     - Loop fusion, distribution\n     - Vectorization (SLP, Loop vectorization)\n     - ControlHeightReductionPass (O3 only)\n     - LoopSinkPass\n   - Final SimplifyCFG and instruction combining\n\n## Key Files Summary\n\n- **llvm/include/llvm/IR/PassManager.h**: Core template and ModulePassManager definition\n- **llvm/include/llvm/PassRegistry.h**: PassRegistry declaration\n- **llvm/lib/IR/PassRegistry.cpp**: Pass registration implementation\n- **llvm/include/llvm/PassInfo.h**: PassInfo metadata structure\n- **llvm/include/llvm/PassSupport.h**: Registration macros and RegisterPass template\n- **llvm/include/llvm/IR/PassManagerInternal.h**: PassConcept and PassModel implementations\n- **llvm/include/llvm/Passes/PassBuilder.h**: PassBuilder API declaration\n- **llvm/lib/Passes/PassBuilderPipelines.cpp**: Pipeline construction implementations\n- **llvm/include/llvm/InitializePasses.h**: Pass initialization declarations"
